$ /dev/zero

`/dev/zero` is an endless source of `0x00` bytes.

code {
$ → Linux/shell/commands/dd if=/dev/zero bs=20 count=1 2>→ Linux/fhs/dev/null | → Linux/shell/commands/xxd → Linux/shell/commands/xxd#xxd-i[-i]
  0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00,
  0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00
code }

sa:

  Compare with `→ Linux/fhs/dev/null` and `→ Linux/fhs/dev/full`

 `→ Linux/shell/commands/man 4 zero`

 `→ Linux/fhs/dev`
